pageContext.claim: “Part of that was that Barack Hussein Obama allowed me to have 142. We started with 142 empties. I don't think anybody's ever had one. You don't do that. But he left me 142. Couldn't get 'em confirmed.”
pageContext.analysis: There were 88 district and 17 court of appeals vacancies when Trump took office, so a total of 105 -- not through Obama's lack of effort. Senate Republicans refused to move on his nominations.
